name: SOLARIS_120321_1144
description: SOLARIS is a series of artworks generated by solar wind activity from the Deep Space Climate Observatory (DSCOVR), a satellite launched by NASA in February 2015 and monitoring the Sun. Each piece is a real time visualization based on 1-minute averaged Real-time Interplanetary Magnetic Field Values shown on the bottom left. Data provided by National Environmental Satellite, Data, and Information Service (NESDIS).
